############ AC1: consent toggle on the Gateway, default ON, persists across restart ############

### [1] Fresh proof root, no config.json yet -> GET must default ON
--- config dir before any write ---
director/
--- GET /gateway/telemetry-consent ---
{"enabled":true}

### [2] PUT enabled=false (user turns telemetry OFF on the Cockpit/Gateway)
{"enabled":false}
--- GET reflects OFF ---
{"enabled":false}
--- config.json persisted on the Gateway ---
{
  "telemetry_consent": false
}

### [3] Restart the Gateway: stop the process, GET must be unreachable
listener PID=28400 name=ConsentProofGateway
stopped my harness
 <- gateway down (expected)

### [4] After restart: GET re-reads config.json from disk -> must STILL be OFF (persisted across restart)
{"enabled":false}
PASS: the OFF value set before the restart survived (default is ON, so OFF can only come from persisted state).
